<subSubSection pageNumber="257" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="257">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">Note:</emphasis>
Although some authors (e.g. Fawcett &amp; Rendle, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">Fl. Jamaica</emphasis>
3: 136. 1914; Townsend in Polhill, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">
Fl. Trop. E. Africa, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
: 102. 1985) treat the type as from the Hermann herbarium (BM), and therefore homotypic with 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" higherTaxonomySource="Manual Input" rank="variety" variety="aspera">
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">aspera</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Achyranthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="aspera" variety="indica">
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has as the source of its diagnosis a Burman description and figure. In addition, although some authors treat 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Mill." authorityName="Mill." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Achyranthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">A. indica</emphasis>
(L.) Mill.
</taxonomicName>
as synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Achyranthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="257">A. aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, others do not.
</paragraph>
